Heated and Climate Controlled Storage in Basalt

Climate controlled storage in Basalt can make a world of difference for those sensitive belongings. Moving? Your major household appliances dont always care for freezing temperatures, which can have a negative impact on their electrical systems. Documents in commercial storage can be warped and become brittle when exposed to the cold, making it important to keep them in the right storage environment. Choose climate controlled storage for all of your sensitive items.

Ski Equipment Storage Near Aspen, Vail, and Breckenridge

Ski equipment can occupy quite a bit of space in your home, and especially if youre living in a small house or apartment, finding that available space can be a challenge. You might prefer to keep it in the trunk of your car, but ski equipment needs to be stored away from sunlight, heat, and moisture in order to stay in good condition. Within an indoor climate controlled storage unit, your ski equipment will stay in a stable environment that offers increased protection from both the heat and cold. That way, itll be in prime condition when youre ready to hit your favorite skiing spots, such as:
  • Keystone Resort
  • Aspen Mountain Ski Resort
  • Copper Mountain
  • Beaver Creek Resort
  • Vail Ski Resort
  • Breckenridge Ski Resort

FAQs About Storage in Basalt, CO


What are some tips for furniture storage in Basalt, CO?

When storing furniture, first pay attention to the material the furniture is made of. Wood and leather can be temperature-sensitive, and therefore a heated storage unit or climate controlled storage unit may be better suited for your furniture storage.
Additionally, you should separate removable parts, such as the legs of tables and chairs or shelves in cabinets. Protect fragile parts or corners with bubble wrap or other forms of cushioning and lay down towels, blankets, or cardboard to avoid scuffing and moisture from the ground.
